verses.roman:
kaṣṭe-sṛṣṭye kari' gelāṅa rāmakeli-grāma
āmāra ṭhāñi āilā 'rūpa' 'sanātana' nāma

synonyms: kaṣṭe-sṛṣṭye—with great difficulty; kari'-doing; gelāṅa—I went; rāmakeli-grāma—to the village of Rāmakeli; āmāra ṭhāñi—before me; āilā—came; rūpa sanātana nāma—the two brothers named Rūpa and Sanātana.
translation: "With great difficulty I went to the town of Rāmakeli, where I met two brothers named Rūpa and Sanātana.
